changes LGTM ...though there are few scnario's we there could have some latency as we have a single thread handling all these timers ..  If we have asic timer at 5sec .. and for SFP it is 60sec, the same thread does a redis get for a large number of SFP modules (on a DUT with say 512 interfaces) will affect the next polling cycle of asic timer -- since this operation could take > 5 sec ? 

May be we should remove the SFP polling from redis .. now that we would like this optics temperature to be polled by xcvrd itself. We can add a separate thread thermalctld in future if we really need to get the xcvr temperature in thermalctld. 

@vvolam @Junchao-Mellanox  let me know thoughts

